## Server Picker for Linux

A small (32kib source at the time of writing) Linux tool/script to help you **pick or restrict game servers** (e.g., CS2) by applying temporary firewall rules.
It fetches server information from the Steam Web API and can add or remove `iptables` rules to allow or deny traffic to specific server IPs.

## Features

- Fetches server lists from the Steam Web API (read-only HTTP `GET`)
- Applies firewall rules using `iptables`
- Allows restricting connections to selected servers
- Temporary rules (can be reverted)

---

## Requirements

- Linux (does not work on windows) !important

bash
curl
iptables
sudo (soft dependency) application CAN be started as uid=0 (root) and it will function.
jq

---

## Installation

### Clone the repository

git clone https://github.com/keijo0/serverpicker.git
cd serverpicker
chmod +x serverpicker
./serverpicker

It will prompt you for your password in the terminal once you block regions
to reset firewall status use the "Reset Firewall" button and you should be able to continue your journey.
